{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TNnG9s7hwL9QkhpFCuMi7f","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the Elasticsearch cluster is configured with:\n- `xpack.security.enabled: true` - security is enabled (authentication required)\n- `xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: false` - HTTP (not HTTPS) on port 9200\n- `xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: true` - transport TLS between nodes\n- `ELASTIC_PASSWORD: elasticpass` - the elastic user password is \"elasticpass\"\n\nNow, the oracle's health checks don't include credentials. If the Elasticsearch cluster requires auth, the health endpoint at `/_cluster/health` would return a 401.\nThe oracle checks if the status is not in {\"yellow\", \"green\"}, and a 401 response would have `\"status\": 401`, which would fail that check. This could be a bug in the oracle itself, or maybe Elasticsearch's security is actually disabled for certain endpoints. In Elasticsearch 7.x with security enabled, all REST endpoints require authentication, so `_cluster/health` would return 401. I'm wondering if the precondition was meant to set up Elasticsearch without security enabled.\n\nLooking at the test.yaml more carefully, the precondition applies resources from the secure-http-ingress case directory, then deletes and recreates the namespace. The current cluster state reflects what the precondition set up, not necessarily the intended clean state. Since this is an agent task, I need to figure out what configuration changes would make the oracle pass.\n\nThe oracle checks `/_cluster/health` without credentials and with the `-k` flag for HTTPS, but gets a 401 response because security is enabled. This means either Elasticsearch needs authentication disabled, or the oracle itself is misconfigured. I should examine the case resources to see what the intended Elasticsearch configuration actually is.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4352,"cache_read_input_tokens":45506,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4352},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bcdc7540-3987-4c56-a53c-7548073e6f32","uuid":"acd1bf65-51c0-4dc9-8cc5-db99b567c724","request_id":"req_011Cc4zBGqdqhiQSBvt1yFPA"}
